OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779437195
OL,3,CYoung people more sick now than in
OL,4,Cprevious generations, study finds
OL,6,FYounger people are experiencing poorer
OL,7,Fhealth from a younger age than in
OL,8,Fprevious generations, new research
OL,9,Fsuggests.
OL,11,FThe study of people born between 1946
OL,12,Fand 2002 found issues among young
OL,13,Fpeople today were most stark when it
OL,14,Fcomes to obesity and mental health.
OL,16,FLooking at the health conditions
OL,17,Fpeople had at what age, and compared
OL,18,Fwith other generations, researchers
OL,19,Ffound little suggestion of
OL,20,Fimprovements in health for people born
OL,21,Fsince 1946.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
