CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779437195
OL,3,CYoung people more sick now than in
OL,4,Cprevious generations, study finds
OL,6,FThe experts from University College
OL,7,FLondon (UCL), King's College London
OL,8,Fand the University of Oxford suggest
OL,9,Fthe "generational health drift" will
OL,10,Fhave implications for people working
OL,11,Fand supporting the economy.
OL,13,FFor several outcomes ` particularly
OL,14,Fobesity, mental ill health and
OL,15,Fdiabetes, "prevalence of poor health
OL,16,Fwas higher in more recent
OL,17,Fgenerations", the study of more than
OL,18,F88,500 people found.
OL,26,@wD@KOUyD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
