PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779437195
OL,3,CYoung people more sick now than in
OL,4,Cprevious generations, study finds
OL,6,F"Long-term declines in mortality and
OL,7,Ffertility mean that by 2050, one
OL,8,Fquarter of the British population will
OL,9,Fbe aged 65 and over, with considerable
OL,10,Fimplications for future demand for
OL,11,Fhealth and social care and also for
OL,12,Fthe economy," the team said.
OL,14,F"Ensuring that more recently born
OL,15,Fcohorts both live longer and do so in
OL,16,Fgood health is important for facing
OL,17,Fthe challenges of population ageing."
OL,19,FThe findings, published in the journal
OL,20,FPopulation Studies, included data from
OL,21,F51 studies published up to June 2024.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@MO]vD@AOUyD@eO]
