PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779437195
OL,3,CYoung people more sick now than in
OL,4,Cprevious generations, study finds
OL,6,F"If more recent generations are
OL,7,F'drifting' backwards in health, it
OL,8,Fimplies that society is not reaching
OL,9,Fthe biological limits of health
OL,10,Fimprovement but rather seeing the
OL,11,Fconsequences of preventable social and
OL,12,Fenvironmental exposures that have
OL,13,Fshaped population health over time and
OL,14,Facross generations.
OL,16,F"The generational health drift has
OL,17,Fserious implications for policy,
OL,18,Fplanning and the funding allocations
OL,19,Fneeded to be able to support a greater
OL,20,Fnumber of people living with chronic
OL,21,Fhealth conditions."
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU}D@SO]
